OpenPhone Source-Available License Notice

This repository contains multiple categories of code and documentation.

1. OpenPhone-owned code and documentation

   Unless a file says otherwise, OpenPhone-owned files in this repository are
   provided for non-commercial use only. Commercial use requires a separate
   written license from the OpenPhone project owner.

   This temporary project license is intentionally conservative while the
   commercial licensing model is finalized. Before public release, replace this
   file with a complete source-available license, such as a finalized custom
   OpenPhone license or an established license like PolyForm Noncommercial.

2. Upstream Android, LineageOS, Linux kernel, and third-party code

   Upstream code keeps its original license. OpenPhone does not relicense code
   it did not create. Apache, BSD, MIT, GPL, proprietary vendor blob, and other
   notices must be preserved according to the relevant upstream license.

3. GPL-covered code

   GPL-covered code and modifications remain subject to the GPL. OpenPhone does
   not add non-commercial restrictions to GPL-covered code.

4. Commercial licensing

   Commercial use of OpenPhone-owned code requires a separate license.

